 Jordanian Foreign Minister Ayman Safadi (R) meets with his visiting counterpart of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Abdullah bin Zayed al-Nahyan in Amman, Jordan, Nov. 10, 2021. (Photo by Mohammad Abu Ghosh/Xinhua) AMMAN, Nov. 10 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Foreign Minister Ayman Safadi and his visiting counterpart of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Abdullah bin Zayed al-Nahyan on Wednesday discussed means to enhance cooperation between the two countries in all fields. The two ministers voiced keenness to seek broader cooperation in the economic, investment, tourism, cultural and defense fields, with practical steps to realize the envisioned goals, according to a statement by the Jordanian foreign ministry. They stressed the importance of continuing coordination over regional issues and the efforts to overcome common challenges and solve regional crises in a bid to achieve Middle East security and stability. Safadi expressed Jordan's pride in the distinguished ties with the UAE, praising its consistent solidarity with Jordan and continuous support for the kingdom's efforts to overcome economic challenges. Sheikh Abdullah also reaffirmed pride in ties between the two countries and leaderships, noting that the UAE highly appreciates the main role of Jordan in enhancing the joint Arab action and achieving stability. Also on Wednesday, King Abdullah II of Jordan and Sheikh Abdullah discussed efforts for political solutions to regional crises, and coordination and consultation over issues of mutual concern, especially the Palestinian cause. Enditem